  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will include 60 patients with early breast cancer referred to receive adjuvant
      chemotherapy with AC ( adriamycin- cyclophosphamide) or CAF ( adriamycin- cyclophosphamide-
      5- fluorouracil ) combinations. These patients will receive every day one spoon of Lifemel
      honey or regular honey ( double blind)- during the adjuvant chemotherapy .Every week a WBC
      count will be performed in order to record the influence of Lifemel on myelotoxicity.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
